description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshtastic/codec.c:430-446

  static int copy_tmp_payload(const uint8_t *tmp, size_t len,
                              uint8_t *buf, size_t buflen)
  {
      if (buf == NULL) {
          return -EINVAL;
      }
      if (len > LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_FROM_RADIO_MAX) {
          return -EMSGSIZE;
      }
      if (buflen < len) {
          return -ENOMEM;
      }
      if (len > 0U) {
          memcpy(buf, tmp, len);
      }
      return (int)len;  // Cast size_t to int
  }

The function returns (int)len. LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_FROM_RADIO_MAX is 510, which fits in int. So this is technically safe.

However, the check 'len > LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_FROM_RADIO_MAX' depends on the macro value being smaller than INT_MAX. If CONFIG_LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_MAX_FROM_RADIO is defined to a large value (>INT_MAX), the cast would overflow.

Add a static assertion:
  BUILD_ASSERT(LICHEN_MESHTASTIC_FROM_RADIO_MAX <= INT_MAX, 'max must fit in int');
